# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  05 - Authentication & Headers
#  Real-world APIs require authentication.
#  These show the most common patterns.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@baseUrl    = https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com
@token      = your-jwt-token-here
@apiKey     = your-api-key-here
@username   = admin
@password   = password123

# ── 1. Bearer Token (JWT) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Most modern APIs use this. The server validates the token.

### Bearer Token Auth
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json


# ── 2. API Key in Header ──────────────────────────────────────
# Secure — key is not visible in the URL or browser history.

### API Key via Custom Header
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/1
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json


# ── 3. API Key in Query Param ─────────────────────────────────
# Less secure — key appears in URL and server logs.

### API Key via Query Parameter
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/1?apikey={{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json


# ── 4. Basic Auth ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# username:password encoded as Base64 in the Authorization header.
# Format: Basic <base64(username:password)>
# Example: admin:password123 → YWRtaW46cGFzc3dvcmQxMjM=

### Basic Auth
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/1
Authorization: Basic YWRtaW46cGFzc3dvcmQxMjM=
Accept: application/json


# ── 5. Multiple Headers ───────────────────────────────────────
# Real requests often send several headers together.

### Request with Multiple Headers
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: req-001
X-Client-Version: 1.0.0
Cache-Control: no-cache


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Common HTTP Status Codes Reference:
#
#  2xx — Success
#    200 OK           — request succeeded
#    201 Created      — resource created (POST)
#    204 No Content   — success, no body (DELETE)
#
#  3xx — Redirection
#    301 Moved Permanently
#    302 Found (temporary redirect)
#
#  4xx — Client Errors
#    400 Bad Request  — invalid input
#    401 Unauthorized — missing or invalid credentials
#    403 Forbidden    — authenticated but not allowed
#    404 Not Found    — resource doesn't exist
#    422 Unprocessable Entity — validation failed
#
#  5xx — Server Errors
#    500 Internal Server Error
#    503 Service Unavailable
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
